feat(recovery): idempotent turn-replay, UI banner, and legacy-table ORM coverage

Safe replay of post-narrative bookkeeping
- src/core/turn_replay.py (new): replay_safe_bookkeeping() re-runs ONLY the
  idempotent subset (entity_graph_snapshot, memory_heat_decay) for a turn
  whose background processing crashed. Non-idempotent steps
  (combat/consequence/progression/episodic memory) land in skipped_steps
  with explicit reasons; replay errors surface in the result without
  aborting the other steps.
- src/core/_background.py: instrument each post-narrative step with a
  completed_steps marker. Both completion and crash paths now persist the
  list into the gameplay_turn_checkpoint artifact, so replay can tell
  exactly which steps completed before the crash.
- api/routes/game/status.py: new POST /session/{id}/replay-bookkeeping
  endpoint that invokes the replay on the active orchestrator and returns
  a structured summary (replayed / skipped / errors / already_done).
  Clears Orchestrator.incomplete_turn when the idempotent cover set is
  fully restored so /status stops surfacing the banner.
- tests/test_turn_replay.py (new): six-case coverage of
  no-incomplete-turn no-op, idempotent re-run + checkpoint update + flag
  clear, skip-already-done, non-idempotent-reasons listing, error
  surfacing, and partial-replay-keeps-flag-set semantics.

Frontend recovery banner
- web/js/app.js: checkIncompleteTurn() prepends a dismissable banner to
  the narrative on session resume when GET /status returns incomplete_turn.
  Banner renders turn number, intent, action, and player-input preview.
  Replay-safe-steps button calls the new endpoint and shows the
  replayed/skipped summary inline. Dismiss button writes a per-turn
  localStorage key so the banner stays gone after the player acknowledges.
- web/css/main.css: .recovery-banner palette + button treatment.
- web/js/api.js: Game.replayBookkeeping() wrapper.

ORM coverage for alembic-only tables
- src/db/models.py: add CampaignMemory, ContextBlock, ProfileLoreChunk,
  CustomProfileLoreChunk, RuleLibraryChunk. These mirror the tables
  created by alembic 005/006 but were previously ORM-less, which left
  dangling campaigns-FK dependents that blocked Base.metadata.drop_all().
  Vector columns (pgvector, no native SQLAlchemy type) stay out of the
  ORM; they're read/written via raw SQL elsewhere.
- tests/conftest.py fresh_db docstring updated; no behavior change.

Settings test follow-up
- tests/settings/test_session_zero_agent_models.py: the old list assumed
  every SZ compiler agent belongs to THINKING_TIER. Since the scope was
  trimmed (review.txt, 2026-03-12) and the resolver+gap merge landed
  (4b306bb), sz_extractor and sz_resolver_and_gap are fast-tier, and
  only sz_handoff + session_zero are thinking-tier. Tests now reflect
  that split.

Test stability
- tests/test_crash_recovery.py, tests/test_gameplay_checkpoint.py: depend
  on fresh_db so the SessionZeroArtifact schema is guaranteed to exist
  regardless of which DATABASE_URL wins during pytest collection
  (test_deferred_commit.py hard-sets sqlite at import time, which can
  flip the cached engine mid-suite). Dropped a caplog assertion in
  test_incomplete_turn_returns_data; the returned dict already proves
  the log path executed.

Result: 363 passed on the full SZ + recovery + settings suite.

